# video drivers
xf86-video-vesa:
            xf86-video-vesa which is a fallback driver for very old machines. You also don't need xf86-video-intel if you have a recent (Sandy Bridge+) Intel graphics card, because those are better supported by the generic modesetting driver that's built into Xorg.

